                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 161.) On the 30th of June, about a quarter-past four o'clock, I took these boots from the prisoner in the West-minister-road—he said he bought them in the New Cut, for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was coming up the Cut from the Baths; a man asked me to buy these, and I gave him 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for them; the office asked me to show them to him, and I did; he took me to the station.</p>
